      "message": "\u003e * @param[in] pin The maximum supported package format revision of the caller\n\nWhat if we dropped this PIN argument entirely from the C++ API.\n\nI can imagine many callers are not terribly interest in specific revisions\nand instead just need to know if a given fields exists in the libpldm++ they are linked against.\n\nFor that purpose we have `HasMember` function from `GrowableStruct`.\n\nCurrently they don\u0027t need to use that though since we only support v1.0 for now.\n\n\n\u003e I\u0027d rather develop equivalent pins for the C++ API so it can evolve independently of the C API\n\nWith \u0027equivalent\u0027 you mean copy-pasting it with a different name?\n\nOr should we start with e.g. `LIBPLDMPP_PKG_PIN_1` and then increment from there and translate internally to some libpldm pin.",
